I'm unable to create files directly, but I can provide you with the code for a simple `index.html` file that contains a "Hello World" message styled in a dark theme with bold colors. You can copy the following code into a new file and save it as `index.html`.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Hello World</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #121212;
            color: #ffffff;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
        }

        .hello-world {
            font-size: 48px;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #ff5722; /* A striking orange-red */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="hello-world">Hello World!</div>
</body>
</html>
```

To create the file:

1. Open a text editor of your choice (e.g., Notepad, VS Code, Sublime Text).
2. Copy and paste the above code into the text editor.
3. Click "File" â†’ "Save As".
4. Name the file `index.html`.
5. Choose where to save it on your computer.

After saving, you can open this HTML file in any web browser to see the styled "Hello World" message.
